@startuml
title BEACON - System Context (C1)

!include ../styles/theme-simple.puml

actor "Admin" as admin

rectangle "BEACON\n<size:11>IoT Wi-Fi analytics cluster</size>" as beacon {
}

cloud "Building Wi-Fi\nInfrastructure" as wifi {
}

node "iPerf Server\n<size:11>Throughput test endpoint</size>" as iperf {
}

database "NTP / DNS\n<size:11>Network services</size>" as ntp

admin -right-> beacon : Configure probes,\nview dashboards
beacon -up-> wifi : Collect Wi-Fi metrics
beacon -right-> iperf : Active throughput\n& latency tests
beacon -down-> ntp : Time sync,\nname resolution

note right of beacon
  Deployables inside BEACON:
  • Raspberry Pi probe agents
  • GraphQL API + config store
  • Prometheus + Grafana stack
end note

note right of iperf
  Optional component for active testing.
  Only needed if you want to run
  throughput or latency tests.
end note

@enduml